post_text:
It is our mission to make sure that every student in Alabama is able to access their education. The Alabama Broadband Connectivity for Students Program is here to help get your household set up for distance learning. All you need to do is follow 4 steps.
Step 1: Once you receive your ABC voucher letter in the mail, call a participating internet service provider listed on your voucher letter.
Step 2: Tell the internet service provider: "I have an Alabama ABC Voucher" and provide the number on the top of your letter.
Step 3: Your internet service provider will provide any equipment or installation you may need. Don‚Äôt worry, they will talk you through the process and the costs are covered by the voucher.
Step 4: Once service begins, help your student get online so they can be ready to start learning.
Be on the lookout for this letter! Inside, your voucher letter will give you all the information you need to get set up with your free high speed internet.

post_text: Congratulations to Selma High School‚Äôs environmental science students Janiyha Minniefield and Jimaya Nunn. They won first place at Tuskegee University‚Äôs EXERT Agriculture Farm Competition amongst 5 other counties under the supervision of Mr. Irby and Mrs.Tempero-Culliver. For this competition, students were employed to create and present a farm with a $20,000 budget and 10 acres of land. Minniefield and Nunn chose to build a vegetable farm called the ‚ÄúSaintly Vegetable Farm‚Äù with a strategic mission to support the homeless people in the local Selma area and to increase healthy food access for the inner city community. Awesome job ladies! #TeamSelma
text: Congratulations to Selma High School‚Äôs environmental science students Janiyha Minniefield and Jimaya Nunn.
